# Open Graph images

## Field conventions

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `banner` | On-page hero image (`_layouts/case-study.html` only) |
| `og_image` | Social preview only — never rendered on the page |

`_includes/head.html` resolves `og:image` / `twitter:image` in this order:

1. `page.og_image`
2. `page.banner`
3. Fallback: `/assets/meta/an-og.jpg?v=3`

## Which field to use

**Static pages & regular posts** (no on-page hero):
- Use `banner: /assets/metadata/...` or `og_image: /assets/metadata/...`
- Either works; `og_image` is clearer, `banner` is fine as shorthand

**Case studies** (`layout: case-study`):
- Use `banner` (+ `banner-mobile`) for the on-page hero **and** for OG/social
- Do **not** set `og_image` — `head.html` falls back to `banner` automatically
- Do not capture screenshot OG images for case studies

```
Need on-page hero?     → banner (+ banner-mobile)
Want custom social?    → og_image (not used on case studies)
Happy with hero as OG? → banner only (case studies)
Regular page/post?     → banner or og_image
```

## Screenshots

Playwright captures at **1024×694**, dark mode. Saved to:
- `assets/metadata/` — static pages
- `assets/metadata/posts/` — blog posts

## Prerequisites

- Jekyll running locally: `bundle exec jekyll serve`
- Playwright installed once: `npm install && npx playwright install chromium`

## Commands

```bash
node scripts/capture-og.mjs /listening listening-og   # single page
npm run capture-all-og                                 # static pages (not homepage or /now)
npm run capture-posts-og                               # all _posts/ (updates front matter)
```

Override viewport with `OG_WIDTH`, `OG_HEIGHT`, `OG_BASE_URL`.

## New static page

1. `node scripts/capture-og.mjs /page-path page-og`
2. Add `banner: /assets/metadata/page-og.png` (or `og_image`)
3. Add to `scripts/capture-all-og.mjs` for batch regeneration

Skip homepage (`/`, `/en/`, `/el/`) and `/now` (content changes often).

## New blog post

After the post is reachable at `/{category}/{slug}.html`:

- **Regular post:** `banner: /assets/metadata/posts/{slug}-og.png`
- **Case study:** `banner` (+ `banner-mobile`) only — same image for hero and OG; skip screenshot capture

Or run `npm run capture-posts-og` (skips case studies; sets `banner` on other posts).
